23/06/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) Security Minister Sadik Ahmetovic met on Tuesday (June 22nd) in Brussels with EU Home Affairs Commissioner Cecilia Malmstrom.
They both expressed satisfaction with BiH's progress in meeting obligations under its EU visa liberalisation road map.
Malstrom said she has no doubts that the country will meet the remaining conditions before the expected arrival of EU experts in July.
They will assess BiH's readiness for inclusion in the visa-free travel regime.
Ahmetovic voiced confidence that the experts will confirm BiH's progress in meeting visa-liberalisation criteria.
(Fena, Sarajevo-x.com - 22/06/10)
